title: Packers Hold 49ers to a Field Goal
text:
Packers Hold 49ers to a Field Goal 
  Packers Hold 49ers to a Field Goal October 5, 2015 Updated Oct 5, 2015 at 12:07 AM CDT 
Santa Clara, CA (NNCNOW.com) -- The Green Bay Packers put their undefeated record on the line against the San Francisco 49ers, and came away while holding the team to a lone field goal. 
Aaron Rodgers displayed awareness and footwork as he evaded linemen in a broken-down pocket to complete the game's first touchdown to Richard Rodgers.
